The paper deals with the problem of adaptively searching for an unknown target using multiple agents connected through a time-varying network topology. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Multiagent Systems (cs.MA), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). However, given the focus on decentralized collaborative algorithms and social learning, cs.MA and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The use of martingale-based techniques and spectral graph theory for convergence analysis also suggests a potential fit with cs.SY. The paper's emphasis on scalability and low complexity methods aligns with cs.DS, while the use of randomized pairwise averaging and performance guarantees aligns with cs.LG.
